  <Fragment slot="heading">Security and Trust</Fragment>
  <Fragment slot="summary">AGYL is designed so each customer’s records, standards, and operational intelligence remain isolated and governed by that customer.</Fragment>

  <h2>Architecture</h2>
  <p>AGYL is designed so each customer's records and customer-specific context are isolated from other customers, and customer data is not used to train models that serve another customer.</p>

  <h2>Core controls</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Encryption in transit and at rest.</li>
    <li>Role-based access appropriate to the deployed environment.</li>
    <li>Traceable decisions and audit records for governed changes.</li>
    <li>Customer-controlled thresholds for decisions that require review.</li>
    <li>Vendor and access review as part of the operating security program.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Compliance posture</h2>
  <p>AGYL maintains a security program aligned with the trust commitments presented on this site, including SOC 2 controls and support for applicable GDPR and CCPA obligations. The exact controls, reports, data-processing terms, and deployment responsibilities for a client engagement are provided during security review and governed by the applicable agreement.</p>

  <h2>Responsible reporting</h2>
  <p>If you believe you have found a security issue involving AGYL, do not include sensitive customer data in your initial message. Send a concise description to <a href="mailto:info@agyl.ai">info@agyl.ai</a>, and we will coordinate a secure follow-up channel.</p>
</LegalPage>
